      "content": "85% seems pretty high, though. I was just looking over the raw telemetry from the last three patient cohorts in the Phase II group, and the variance in the biomarker response levels looks pretty wide to me. It actually looks like some of the mid-stage responders are dropping off significantly. Doesn't that variance suggest we might be looking at a much wider margin of error than 15%?",
